  "final_answer": "## Implied Monthly Starlink ARPU Estimate — Q1 2026\n\n### Methodology\n\nThe filing directly discloses a **Starlink Subscriber ARPU of $66/month** for Q1 2026. However, this is computed from a **narrowly defined** revenue and subscriber base. Below, I reconstruct what a user would arrive at using the broader **Connectivity segment revenue** with the disclosed subscriber counts, identify the resulting overstatement, and enumerate every exclusion.\n\n---\n\n### 1. Data Inputs\n\n| Metric | Q1 2026 | Q1 2025 | Source |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Connectivity Segment Revenue | $3,257M | $2,475M | Segment revenue table |\n| Less: Products Revenue (Starlink Kit Sales) | ($380M) | ($352M) | Disaggregated revenue table |\n| **Connectivity Service Revenue** | **$2,877M** | **$2,123M** | Calculated |\n| Starlink Subscribers (end of period) | 10.3M | 5.0M | Segment data |\n| Starlink Subscribers (beginning of period = prior year-end) | 8.9M | 4.4M | Segment data |\n| **Average Starlink Subscribers (simple midpoint)** | **9.6M** | **4.7M** | Calculated: (beginning + ending) / 2 |\n\n---\n\n### 2. Implied ARPU Calculations\n\n**Scenario A — Total Connectivity Revenue (incl. products & enterprise/government):**\n\n$$\\text{Implied ARPU} = \\frac{\\$3{,}257\\text{M}}{9.6\\text{M} \\times 3\\text{ months}} = \\$113.09/\\text{month}$$\n\n**Scenario B — Connectivity Service Revenue (excluding product/kit sales):**\n\n$$\\text{Implied ARPU} = \\frac{\\$2{,}877\\text{M}}{9.6\\text{M} \\times 3\\text{ months}} = \\$99.90/\\text{month}$$\n\n**Scenario C — Disclosed Starlink Subscriber ARPU (filing's own metric):**\n\n$$\\text{Disclosed ARPU} = \\$66/\\text{month}$$\n\n---\n\n### 3. Reconciliation of the Gap\n\n| Component | Q1 2026 | % of Connectivity Service Revenue |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Starlink Subscriber Service Revenue** (backed into: $66 × 9.6M × 3) | $1,901M | 66.1% |\n| **Enterprise & Government Service Revenue** (residual) | $976M | 33.9% |\n| **Total Connectivity Service Revenue** | $2,877M | 100.0% |\n| **Product Revenue (Starlink Kit Sales)** | $380M | excluded from ARPU numerator |\n| **Total Connectivity Segment Revenue** | $3,257M | — |\n\nThe implied ARPU of **$99.90/month** (Scenario B) overstates the filing's disclosed Starlink Subscriber ARPU of **$66/month** by approximately **$34/month (51%)** because the Connectivity service revenue denominator includes enterprise and government revenue from customers who are **not** counted as Starlink Subscribers.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Assumptions\n\n1. **Average subscriber count = simple midpoint** of beginning-of-period (8.9M at Dec 31, 2025) and end-of-period (10.3M at Mar 31, 2026), yielding 9.6M. The filing states it uses \"average number of Starlink Subscribers during the period\" but does not disclose monthly granularity; the midpoint is the best available approximation. To the extent subscriber growth was front- or back-loaded within Q1 2026, the true average would differ.\n\n2. **Q1 2026 beginning subscribers = FY2025 ending subscribers (8.9M).** This assumes no restatement or adjustment between the periods.\n\n3. **Product revenue is excluded** from the service-revenue-based ARPU calculation (Scenario B) to better approximate the recurring subscription revenue base. The filing confirms all product revenue is attributable to the Connectivity segment and represents one-time Starlink Kit sales.\n\n---\n\n### 5. What the Filing's Subscriber Count and Revenue Definitions Exclude\n\nThe filing's **disclosed Starlink Subscriber ARPU ($66/month)** differs from a naïve Connectivity revenue-based calculation because of the following exclusions:\n\n#### A. Excluded from the Starlink Subscriber Count (denominator):\n- **Managed enterprise customers** with direct, negotiated agreements through the Starlink sales team — including:\n  - Aviation customers\n  - Maritime customers\n  - Land mobility customers\n  - Fixed-site enterprise customers\n- **Government / Starshield customers** under long-term, multi-year contracts\n- These customers are **not** counted even though they consume Connectivity services\n\nThe subscriber count reflects only **unique Service Lines** tied to a consumer-facing Starlink.com account, encompassing Personal (Residential, Roam) and Business (Local Priority, Global Priority) plans.\n\n#### B. Excluded from the Starlink Subscriber ARPU Numerator:\n- **Enterprise & Government service revenue** ($976M in Q1 2026) — from aviation, maritime, land mobility, fixed sites, and Starshield contracts\n- **Starlink Mobile (satellite-to-mobile) revenue** — derived from revenue-sharing arrangements with Mobile Network Operator (MNO) partners, covering ~7.4 million monthly unique devices\n- **Product revenue** ($380M in Q1 2026) — one-time Starlink Kit hardware sales\n\nThe ARPU numerator contains **only** recurring service revenue from the self-service Starlink Subscriber base.\n\n#### C. Additional Metric Nuance:\n- A Starlink \"Subscriber\" = 1 **Service Line**, not 1 person. The filing states the number of individual end users \"is already likely meaningfully higher than 10.3 million,\" as multiple users may share a single Service Line (e.g., a household).\n\n---\n\n### 6. Summary Table\n\n| Measure | Q1 2026 | Q1 2025 | Δ YoY |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **Implied ARPU — Total Connectivity Revenue** | **$113.09/mo** | $175.53/mo | -35.6% |\n| **Implied ARPU — Connectivity Service Revenue** | **$99.90/mo** | $150.57/mo | -33.6% |\n| **Disclosed Starlink Subscriber ARPU** | **$66.00/mo** | $86.00/mo | -23.3% |\n| **Overstatement of naïve vs. disclosed ARPU** | **$33.90/mo (51%)** | $64.57/mo (75%) | — |\n\nThe overstatement narrowed from Q1 2025 to Q1 2026, suggesting the Starlink Subscriber base is growing faster than the enterprise/government revenue base, which is consistent with the filing's disclosure that consumer subscriber growth (105% YoY) outpaced enterprise revenue growth.\n\n---\n\n### Sources\n\n- SpaceX S-1 Filing (May 20, 2026): https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1181412/000162828026036936/spaceexplorationtechnologi.htm",
